daily_summary.headline: Exciting Day for Space Enthusiasts: GPS III Launch and Aurora Opportunities

top_events.title: Falcon 9 Block 5 | GPS III SV09 Launch
top_events.description: SpaceX is set to launch the GPS III SV09 satellite for the US Space Force, enhancing global navigation capabilities.
top_events.action: Watch live stream for real-time coverage.

top_events.title: Aurora Viewing Opportunity
top_events.description: A G1 geomagnetic storm may provide aurora visibility at high latitudes, with the best viewing window from 12:00 to 21:00 UTC.
top_events.action: Check local conditions and head to dark, northern locations for best viewing.

top_events.title: Starlink Group 17-19 Launch
top_events.description: SpaceX continues its Starlink mission with the launch of another batch of satellites, expanding global internet coverage.
top_events.action: Follow the live stream for updates.

opportunities.recommendation: Possible aurora at high latitudes. Best for northern locations (65°+). Worth checking if conditions are optimal.
